genresAdvancedInfo.name: steelpan
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Steelpan is a genre of music that originated in Trinidad and Tobago and is played on a percussion instrument called a steelpan. It is a type of Caribbean music that is characterized by its upbeat rhythms and catchy melodies. Steelpan music is often played during festivals and celebrations and is enjoyed by people of all ages.
